  "texts": [
    "Our findings indicated a slight degradation in the performance of the BPLLM pipeline.",
    "However, through fine-tuning the LLM on both models, the adverse effects were mitigated, demonstrating improved accuracy.Conversely, when incorporating two similar process models, such as Food Delivery and E-commerce, we observed a more significant decline in accuracy for both the base BPLLM pipeline and the pipeline utilizing the fine-tuned LLM.",
    "This outcome was expected, as the LLM's decision-making process can be influenced by the similarities in activity names between the process models, leading to potential misinterpretations.Table 5 reports the results of the previously discussed experiments.",
    "These findings underscore the importance of carefully managing the size and composition of the knowledge base within the LLM, particularly when incorporating multiple process models with varying degrees of similarity.",
    "Additionally, our results highlight the potential benefits of fine-tuning the LLM to enhance its adaptability and performance across diverse process contexts."
  ],
